This is my comparative visualization of Pedestrian vs Vehicular police incidents.¶

The legend is interactive and filters by precinct, the tooltips show the precinct, disposition, and outcome of the incident.

In [32]:
selection = alt.selection(type = "multi", fields=['district'], bind='legend')
# base = alt.Chart(pedestrian).properties(width=450, height=250)
base = alt.Chart(pedestrian)

ped = base.mark_line(point = True).encode(
    x = "date",
    y = "count()",
#     size = "outcome",
    color = alt.condition(selection, "district", alt.value('lightgray')),
#     strokeDash = "precinct",
    tooltip = ["precinct", "disposition", "outcome"]
).add_selection(selection).transform_filter(selection)

veh = alt.Chart(vehicular).mark_line(point = True).encode(
    x = "date",
    y = "count()",
#     size = "outcome",
    color = alt.condition(selection, "district", alt.value('lightgray')),
#     strokeDash = "precinct",
    tooltip = ["precinct", "disposition", "outcome"]
).add_selection(selection).transform_filter(selection)


# alt.vconcat(ped, veh).save('wa8.html')
alt.vconcat(ped, veh)
